Report of the Committee on Rules, Privileges and Elections approving the appointment by the Mayor of ELIZABETH RYAN as a member of the New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission.

The Committee on Rules, Privileges and Elections respectfully reports:

Pursuant to sections 31 and 3020 of the New York City Charter, the Committee on Rules, Privileges and Elections, hereby approves the appointment by the Mayor of ELIZABETH RYAN as a member of the New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission to serve for a term expiring on June 28, 2005.

This matter was referred to the Committee on January 7, 2004.

Res. No. 1

RESOLUTION APPROVING THE APPOINTMENT BY THE MAYOR OF ELIZABETH RYAN AS A MEMBER OF THE NEW YORK CITY LANDMARKS PRESERVATION COMMISSION.

By Council Member Comrie

RESOLVED, that pursuant to sections 31 and 3020 of the New York City Charter, the Council does hereby approve the appointment by the Mayor of ELIZABETH RYAN as a member of the New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission for a term expiring on June 28, 2005.
Items.ActionText: This Resolution was Approved, by Council
Items.MatterName: M 5 - Elizabeth Ryan, Landmarks Preservation Commission
